places of civilization, it saw the world's earliest cities and empires, writing and literature, science and mathematics, monumental art, and innumerable other innovations. Civilizations of Ancient Iraq gives special attention to these milestones, as well as to political, social, and economic history. And because archaeology is the source of almost everything we know about ancient Iraq, the book includes an epilogue on the discovery and fate of its antiquities. Compelling and timely, Civilizations of Ancient Iraq is an essential guide to understanding Mesopotamia's central role in the development of human culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCivilization, Assyro-Babylonian. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aAfghanistan.  aAkkadian literature.  aAlexander the Great.  aAmorites.  aAmu Darya River.  aAnnunitum.  aArchimedes screw.  aAssurbanipal.  aAssyriology.  aBabylon, site.  aBalikh River.  aBerlin Museum.  aBritish Museum.  aCarchemish.  aChaldaean Catholics.  aChristianity.  aDamascius.  aEannatum.  aErlenmeyer Collection.  aEsarhaddon.  aGaugamela.  aGnosticism.  aGreek language.  aHammurabi.  aHassuna ware.  aIraq Museum.  aJeremiah.  aJesus.  aJulius Caesar.  aKudur-nahhunte.  aLachish.  aManishtusu.  aNabopolassar.  aaccounting.  aastronomy.  abevel-rimmed bowls.  acaravanserais.  achronicles.  adecipherment.  adomestication.  aeducation.  afamilies.  afertility.  afrankincense.  afurniture.  ahoroscopes.  aiconography.  akudurrus.  aliteracy.  amathematics.  aminstrels.1 aFoster, Karen Polinger, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400832873zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400832873423Coveruhtt